    "extras": [
      "This route lands best as a 9-day Saudi sampler: 2 nights Riyadh, 2 Jeddah, 1 Medina, 2 Al-Ula, then 1 each in Tabuk and Abha.",
      "Hegra, Dadan/Jabal Ikmah and some Old Town heritage walks all work on timed slots, so book official Experience AlUla inventory before locking hotels.",
      "The Jeddah–Medina Haramain train is the smoothest internal transport leg in the kingdom; for Medina–Al-Ula and Al-Ula–Tabuk, a rental car saves substantial friction.",
      "Edge of the World and Wadi Disah are safest in daylight with extra water, offline maps and either a 4x4 or a local driver.",
      "Hotel prices swing sharply around school holidays, Riyadh event weeks and major religious travel periods, so Saudi stays reward earlier booking more than most Gulf routes."
    ],
